# ============================================================================
# Example: Bass Line Patterns
# ============================================================================
#
# This example demonstrates:
# - Walking bass patterns
# - Syncopated rhythms
# - Note duration variation
# - Low MIDI note range (E1-E3: notes 28-52)
# - Articulation through velocity and duration
#
# Bass Line Theory:
# - Walking bass: stepwise motion connecting chord tones
# - Syncopation: accents on off-beats
# - Root-fifth patterns: common in pop/rock
# - Ghost notes: very short, soft notes for groove
#
# ============================================================================


